@flexiarg futon-theory/wyrd
@title Wyrd: Persistent Salience Across Rival Containers
@sigils [🜚/奇]
@keywords wyrd, weird, becoming, modernism, salience, containment, debt, sorry, Norn, three-times, vertere, unresolved-composition, PKD, Heraclitus
@audience futon developers, pattern theorists, literary theorists, VSATARCS readers
@tone analytic-foundational
@factor Keen investigation (dhammavicaya)
@references [futon-theory/futonic-logic futon-theory/structural-tension-as-observation futon-theory/retroactive-canonicalization futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/symbolic-individuation]
@references-extra ["wyrd ← OE weorþan 'to come to pass, become' ← PIE *wert- 'to twist' → Latin vertere" "Norns: Urðr (that-which-has-come-to-pass), Verðandi (in-process-of-happening, present participle of weorþan), Skuld (debt/owed, from Germanic *skul-, cognate English shall/should)" "Heraclitus DK B54: ἁρμονίη ἀφανὴς φανερῆς κρείττων — the unapparent harmony is stronger than the apparent" "salarium → salary; 'worth one's salt'; 鹽 (composition) ↔ 債 (debt) as dual sides of the same ledger"]

! conclusion:
  Weirdness is not anomaly, noise, or contradiction. It is the
  phenomenology of salience that persists across incompatible
  containment regimes — symbolic configurations that remain
  actionable even as they migrate between fiction, theology,
  coincidence, psychiatry, politics, and media, and that no single
  regime can fully stabilize or dismiss. The etymological identity
  wyrd = weorþan = vertere = "that which turns, becomes, comes to
  pass" makes modernism a name for the wyrd-modality itself, not a
  historical period. The three Norns — Urðr (既/already), Verðandi
  (化/becoming), Skuld (應 or 債/owed) — are a three-time
  decomposition where the future is read as debt, providing a futon
  theory avant la lettre: Skuld is the patron of sorrys.edn.

  + context: Agents operate within overlapping symbolic, institutional,
    perceptual, and technical regimes — media systems, fiction,
    theology, bureaucracy, science, memory. Each provides a 部
    (decomposition regime) and may offer 皿 (stabilizing containers).
    The English word "weird" descends from Old English wyrd, a noun
    formed from the verb weorþan ("to come to pass, to become"),
    itself from PIE *wert- ("to twist"), cognate with Latin vertere
    ("to turn"). Wyrd is feminine; the Norse cognate urðr is also the
    name of one of three Norns. The names of the Norns — Urðr ("that
    which has come to pass"), Verðandi (present participle of the
    cognate verb — "that which is in the process of happening"), and
    Skuld ("debt" or "guilt," from Germanic *skul- "to owe," cognate
    with English shall and should) — constitute a three-time
    decomposition where the future is owed rather than merely upcoming.
    Under conditions where 部 multiply faster than 皿 can absorb them,
    the same symbolic configuration may remain actionable across
    several incompatible regimes simultaneously: this is wyrd.

  + HOWEVER: The structural tension above manifests in the following concrete shapes (see substructure).
    + THE-MERE-X-MOVE:
      Systems frequently attempt premature closure by forcing
      salience into a single container — "mere delusion," "mere
      fiction," "mere prophecy," "mere coincidence." This suppresses
      unresolved composition and hides the 間 (honest interval) where
      the instability actually resides. The "mere X" reflex is the
      central anti-pattern. The same discipline appears elsewhere in
      the library: combining-methods-as-diagnostic (don't collapse to
      a single retrieval method); the :prototyping-forward vs
      :technical-debt typing (don't collapse heterogeneous debts into
      one bucket); the audit against "lightweight" as euphemism
      (don't let smooth language collapse mechanism). Wyrd names
      what these disciplines protect.

    + ANTI-PATTERN-INVENTORY:
      - "mere delusion" — psychiatric reduction
      - "mere fiction" — literary reduction
      - "mere coincidence" — statistical reduction
      - "mere prophecy" — theological reduction
      - "mere subjective experience" — phenomenological reduction
      - "mere noise" — signal-processing reduction
      - "mere relevance score" — retrieval reduction (collapse
        MiniLM/structural/temporal into one number)
      - "mere technical debt" — engineering reduction (collapse
        :prototyping-forward and :technical-debt into one bucket)
      Each collapses wyrd into a single 部, suppressing 間.

  + THEN: Operate an explicit move on the named axis (see substructure below); steward the pattern against the declared discipline.
    + DIAGNOSTIC-CRITERION:
      A symbolic configuration is wyrd-salient when it continues
      generating salience after translation between rival containment
      regimes — and no single regime can fully stabilize or dismiss
      it. The operational test: take the configuration, attempt
      sincere reading under each accessible 部, and observe whether
      salience survives migration. If it dies in every regime but
      one, it is anomaly. If it dies in all regimes, it is noise. If
      it makes every regime locally inconsistent, it is contradiction.
      If it remains actionable in multiple incompatible regimes
      simultaneously, it is wyrd.

    + DISTINCTIONS:
      | Phenomenon | Behavior under regime translation |
      | Noise | No persistent salience; signal dies under any 部 |
      | Anomaly | Collapses to a single 部 once that 部 is expanded |
      | Contradiction | Collapses logic; cannot inhabit any 部 consistently |
      | Wyrd | Salience SURVIVES translation across incompatible 部, without collapsing to any one |

      The fourth next-step of the original sketch is discharged here,
      not deferred: wyrd is defined by the survival behavior, not
      by the affective register.

    + THE-THREE-NORNS-AS-THREE-TIMES:
      | Norn | Sense | Glyph | Futon counterpart |
      | Urðr | that-which-has-come-to-pass | 既 | Closure-evidence / HEAD-as-escrow / the proof path's earned past |
      | Verðandi | in-process-of-happening (present participle of weorþan) | 化 | The live writer-action; the consent gate; the becoming-event |
      | Skuld | debt/owed (cognate shall/should) | 應 (modal) or 債 (noun) | The sorry: the typed obligation the present incurs that the future must discharge |

      The three Norns are not a temporal sequence but a decomposition
      of the present moment into its already-completed,
      presently-becoming, and owed-to-the-future aspects. The future
      is read as obligation, not as mere temporal-next. This is the
      move sorrys.edn already makes: a sorry is not "something that
      didn't get done," it is a debt the present incurred, with
      :kind typing the debt-class (:prototyping-forward as one class,
      :technical-debt as another). Skuld is the patron of sorrys.edn.
      The Buddhist 三時 (過去/現在/未來) is too neutral for this work
      — it loses Skuld's owed character, collapsing the future-as-debt
      into future-as-next.

    + THE-DEBT-SALT-PUN:
      "Worth one's salt" descends from Roman salarium — salt-money,
      the etymological root of "salary." 鹽 (salt) is futonic-logic's
      glyph for generative composition: 鹽 = (⿱ 鹵 皿), the
      recognition that potential and container compose under the
      same 部. 債 (debt) is Skuld's substantive counterpart. The pun
      is load-bearing, not decorative: every act of composition (鹽)
      earns both worth (what-the-salt-pays-for) and debt
      (what-the-composition-owes-the-future). Sorries are the 債
      side of the 鹽 ledger. Wyrd-salience is the structural fact
      that no composition completes its bookkeeping in a single 部 —
      the 債 outstanding in regime A may be the 鹽 generative in
      regime B. The Latin/Chinese/Old English pun (salarium / 鹽-債 /
      Skuld-as-shall) is not adornment; it triangulates the same
      ledger structure from three independent linguistic registers,
      which is itself a wyrd-survival test.

    + WYRD-AS-TURNING:
      PIE *wert- "to twist" and Latin vertere "to turn" foreground
      that wyrd is not static unresolvedness but operational
      rotation. The stereolithographic view rotates. The piano roll
      unrolls. The hairball twists. These are not decorative
      kinetics — they are enacted wyrd. Being-in-becoming requires
      turning operations to remain perceptible across regimes. A
      configuration that cannot be turned between containers has
      collapsed; it is no longer wyrd-salient, only locally salient
      in whatever 部 captured it.

    + VSATARCS-AS-WYRD-CHROME:
      The futon stack decomposes by three-Norn surface:
      - Piano roll = Urðr-surface (frozen tape, already-come-to-pass)
      - M-live-geometric-stack = Verðandi-surface (live, becoming)
      - sorrys.edn = Skuld-surface (typed debt, what's owed)

      VSATARCS is the chrome that lets the operator turn between
      these surfaces without collapsing into any single one. Its
      disagreement signal — when MiniLM-cosine, structural retrieval,
      and closure-evidence return different rankings, the
      disagreement IS the signal (validated live on "a sorry
      enterprise") — is wyrd made operationally tractable. The
      "mere relevance" move (collapse to a single retriever) destroys
      it. VSATARCS is, in this pattern's terms, a tool for
      inhabiting 間 across the three Nornic surfaces rather than
      eliminating it.

    + MODERNISM-AS-WYRD-MODALITY:
      Under the etymological reading, modernism is not the
      post-Enlightenment historical period but the condition of
      being-in-becoming itself — the wyrd-modality. Beowulf is
      modernist in this sense: wyrd-saturated, structurally
      continuous with 20th-century modernism in its inhabitation of
      unresolved composition. The intensification narrative
      ("modernity multiplies 部 faster than 皿 can absorb them")
      holds for any high-decomposition-rate regime, not specifically
      the post-1500 era — pre-modern mystery cults, esoteric
      traditions, apocalyptic literatures all surface the same
      structural condition. PKD's mid-20th-century counterfeit-world
      fiction (anamnesis, Flow My Tears Officer Said, VALIS) is a
      modern instance of an old modality.

  + BECAUSE:
    Salience is generated not by isolated symbols but by partial
    compositions (鹽) that survive migration across incompatible 部.
    When the rate of regime-multiplication exceeds the rate of
    container-stabilization, more configurations remain in this
    trans-regime state. The "mere X" reflex exists because
    containing wyrd in a single regime is cognitively cheap and
    politically convenient — but the cost is the destruction of the
    diagnostic signal the wyrd-salience carried. The Norns name what
    we already practice: Urðr is the past we cite as evidence,
    Verðandi is the act we are presently composing, Skuld is the
    debt that composition incurs. Premature closure into any one
    Norn — collapsing Skuld into "future work" or Verðandi into
    "current state" — strips the three-time structure that makes
    composition legible at all.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Extend futon-theory/futonic-logic to handle the three-Norn temporal decomposition explicitly: add Urðr/Verðandi/Skuld as roles alongside 象/部/咅/鹽/間, and articulate the 鹽/債 ledger as a first-class structure]
    next[Test the wyrd-salience criterion against PKD cases: anamnesis, Flow My Tears Officer Said, VALIS-adjacent counterfeit-world structures — does survival-across-regimes hold as a diagnostic?]
    next[Map Heraclitus DK B54 (ἁρμονίη ἀφανὴς φανερῆς κρείττων) onto the pattern: latent structure (ἀφανὴς ἁρμονίη) as the precondition of wyrd-salience]
    next[Apply to distributed-systems and multi-agent ontology drift: when agents operate under incompatible 部, wyrd-salience is the empirical signature of un-merged commitments]
    next[Design accounting that tracks the 鹽/債 ledger explicitly per composition, rather than collapsing to net — sorries.edn schema v3?]
    next[Use as foreword frame for VSATARCS: position the chrome as wyrd-inhabiting rather than wyrd-eliminating; the rotation of the stereolithographic view is enacted vertere]
